						<div class="postbody">I have learned a majority of my 6502 programming from Nerdy Nights which uses the NESASM3 compiler. NESASM3 uses .rsset to start the RAM location and .rs to set aside locations:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; .rsset $0000<br />Var .rs 1 ; Reserve one byte &#40;$0000&#41;</div>
<br />
<br />This is NESASM's way of working with RAM via a macro. What is the 6502 way to do this?</div>

